  7. Short almond nails — is it possible?
  8. Almond nail maintenance tips
  9. FAQ section (generic Q&A)
  10. Nail shape for chubby fingers / short fingers (scattered, not systematic)

- **Content approach:** Competitors overwhelmingly take a "suits almost everyone" stance with vague reassurance. Most generic nail-shape guides, not almond-specific flattery guides. The few almond-specific posts (OPI, WhoWhatWear, GraziaDaily) give good celebrity-nail-artist quotes but still lack a precise, hand-type-by-hand-type breakdown with honest caveats.

- **Visual patterns:** 6–15 images typical; mostly nail design inspo photos, very few hand-comparison visuals showing the shape on different finger types

### Our Strategic Approach
- **Differentiation:** Every competitor either says "almond suits everyone" (lazy) or buries the answer in a generic 12-shape guide (diluted). We answer *specifically for almond*, by each hand variable — finger length, nail bed width, palm shape — with honest YES/MAYBE/SKIP logic rather than blanket reassurance. We also address the lifestyle suitability question, which most competitors fold into a single sentence.
- **Structure plan:** Quiz-style decision path by hand type → honest per-scenario verdict → length and product modifier (natural vs gel vs acrylic) → visual proof concept (show the shape on different hands). No definition filler. Start with the anxiety, answer it fast.
- **Tone direction:** Confident, direct, like a friend who actually knows nails — not a brand trying to sell you on the shape. British-English editorial register throughout.

