## CONTENT STRUCTURE

### H1
Do Almond Nails Actually Suit You? The Honest Guide by Hand Shape and Finger Type

### H2 Structure
1. **Why Everyone Wonders "Will Almond Nails Suit Me?" — And Why Most Guides Don't Actually Answer It**
   *(Hook — validates the anxiety, calls out vague "suits everyone" answers, sets our position)*

2. **What Makes Almond Nails Different From Oval — And Why That Difference Matters for Your Hands**
   *(Brief but critical distinction: taper depth, tip shape, elongating effect — sets up the rest of the guide)*

3. **Do Almond Nails Suit Short Fingers? Here Is the Honest Answer**
   *(Direct, verdict-first — YES with caveats: mid-length works, very short nail bed is the issue not finger length; Kandalec quote support)*

4. **Do Almond Nails Suit Wide Nail Beds or Chubby Fingers?**
   *(The most anxious segment — separate from finger length. Addresses nail bed width as distinct variable; honest MAYBE verdict with modifier: taper counteracts width, length is key, very wide + very short = skip or go oval)*

5. **Do Almond Nails Suit Long, Slender Fingers? And Can They Look Too Dramatic?**
   *(Addresses the less-discussed flip-side anxiety — readers with longer hands worry almond looks "bony" or excessive)*

6. **Do Almond Nails Suit Small Hands? What About Big Hands?**
   *(Palm size as a separate variable — under-covered by competitors. Short almond addresses small hands; coffin vs almond for larger hands)*

7. **How Much Length Do You Actually Need for Almond Nails to Look Right?**
   *(Practical minimum — free edge length, natural vs extension options; links naturally to almond-nails-on-short-natural-nails post)*

8. **The One Thing That Matters More Than Your Hand Shape: Nail Bed Width vs Tip Length Ratio**
   *(Differentiating insight — most competitors ignore this. The taper only "works" visually if there's enough free edge to show the narrowing effect)*

9. **Try Before You Commit: How Press-On Almond Nails Let You Test the Shape on Your Own Hands**
   *(Conversion de-risk section — validates low-commitment testing; links to salon post for when they're ready)*

10. **Once You Know Almond Suits You: What to Tell Your Nail Tech to Get It Right**
    *(Natural internal link hook → what-to-ask-nail-salon-almond-nails)*

11. **Almond Nail Flattery by Hand Type: Quick Reference Guide**
    *(Visual-friendly summary table/matrix — finger length × nail bed width × verdict → image opportunity here)*

### Structure Reasoning
The H2s are mapped directly to the specific anxieties users carry into this search, ordered by emotional intensity (most-common fear first). Each heading is written as a real user query — searchable in its own right — not an editorial category label. The structure moves from anxiety → specific verdict by hand type → practical threshold (length) → testing pathway → salon action. Internal links are embedded where the reader's natural next question leads to the linked post.

### Image Count Suggestion
8–10 images: 1 hero (almond shape overview on varied hands), 1 per major hand-type section (short fingers, wide nail beds, long fingers, small/big hands), 1 comparison flat-lay (almond vs oval taper), 1 press-on test visual, 1 summary reference graphic (the matrix).

